    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - REMOVE - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>There are two (2) bolt sizes. The 1-1/2" bolts are used with the lifting eyes. Note their
                    location.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts from the shifter housing rim (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300715">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300715" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300715" filename="../figg13/G1300715.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Remove Retaining Bolts From Shifter Housing Rim</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To break the gasket seal, jar the shifter housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300715">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shifter housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300716">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300716" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300716" filename="../figg13/G1300716.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Remove Shifter Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">On 18718 models, inspect the alignment bushing; replace if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300716">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the gasket and clean all mounting surfaces of gasket material (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300716">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the three (3) sets of tension springs and balls from the housing top bores are loose,
                tilt the assembly and remove them (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300717">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300717" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300717" filename="../figg13/G1300717.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Remove Tension Springs and Balls</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
